valuable ? - perhaps for somebody who has never had a real eye for other cultures hofstede 's work was and is not really helpful ; perhaps fascinating for those who deal with the issues from the comfortable space of their warm home of office in a western country . for all who want to get a fundamental insight to understanding espec . asian behavior and cultural differences , i highly recommend to start with : `` the geography of thought : how asians and westerners think differently ... and why -- by richard nisbett '' . that 's the stuff that will bring you where hofstede could never dream to be